<subSubSection pageId="139" pageNumber="536" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="139.[1437,2644,2070,2772]" pageId="139" pageNumber="536">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1439,1789,2543,2576]" pageId="139" pageNumber="536">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Endangered on The IUCN Red List. The Tarella White-toothed Shrew has a very limited distribution, and it is mainly threatened by logging operations causing habitat destruction and fragmentation. It occurs in Bwindi Forest Impenetrable National Park in Uganda.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
